xediaFrameRelayMIB.name: xediaFrameRelayMIB
xediaFrameRelayMIB.description: This module defines additional objects for management of Frame Relay in Xedia devices, above and beyond what is defined in the IETF's Frame Relay MIBs.

xfrArpTable.name: xfrArpTable
xfrArpTable.description: The IP Address Translation table used for mapping from IP addresses to physical addresses, in this case frame relay DLCIs. This table contains much of the same information that is in the ipNetToMediaTable.

xfrArpEntry.name: xfrArpEntry
xfrArpEntry.description: Each entry contains one IpAddress to `physical' address equivalence.

xfrArpIfIndex.name: xfrArpIfIndex
xfrArpIfIndex.description: The interface on which this entry's equivalence is effective. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of RFC 1573's ifIndex.

xfrArpNetAddress.name: xfrArpNetAddress
xfrArpNetAddress.description: The IpAddress corresponding to the frame relay DLCI.

xfrArpType.name: xfrArpType
xfrArpType.description: The type of mapping. Setting this object to the value invalid(2) has the effect of invalidating the corresponding entry in the xfrArpEntryTable. That is, it effectively disassociates the interface identified with said entry from the mapping identified with said entry. It is an implementation- specific matter as to whether the agent removes an invalidated entry from the table. Accordingly, management stations must be prepared to receive tabular information from agents that corresponds to entries not currently in use. Proper interpretation of such entries requires examination of the relevant xfrArpEntryType object.

xfrArpDlci.name: xfrArpDlci
xfrArpDlci.description: The DLCI attached to the IP address.

xfrArpIfStack.name: xfrArpIfStack
xfrArpIfStack.description: A description of the interface stack containing this frame relay interface, with the IP interface, the frame relay interface, and the device interface.

xFrCircuitTable.name: xFrCircuitTable
xFrCircuitTable.description: A table containing additional information about specific Data Link Connection Identifiers and corresponding virtual circuits.

xFrCircuitEntry.name: xFrCircuitEntry
xFrCircuitEntry.description: The additional information regarding a single Data Link Connection Identifier.

xfrCompliance.name: xfrCompliance
xfrCompliance.description: The compliance statement for all agents that support this MIB. A compliant agent implements all objects defined in this MIB.

xfrAllGroup.name: xfrAllGroup
xfrAllGroup.description: The set of all accessible objects in this MIB.
